Given that smart contract also burns $FEI as penalty due to Direct Incentives, and disabling multihop means not having to directly interact with $FEI Router SC, it was a no-brainer to test if swapping $TRIBE for $ETH directly on Uniswap with multi-hop disabled would work.

After disabling multihops, swapping $FEI for $TRIBE worked on Uniswap. 

Not sure why, but I presume this had to with not having to call the FEIRouter to swap $ETH for $FEI https://t.co/U3wQvZfFvi
